Sentencas: In an attempt to reduce the oxidation and Cr evaporation rates of solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs), Mn1.4Co1.4Cu0.2O4 spinel coating is developed on the Crofer22 APU ferritic stainless steel substrate by a powder reduction technique.
Titulo: Mn1.4Co1.4Cu0.2O4 spinel protective coating on ferritic stainless steels for solid oxide fuel cell interconnect applications

Sentencas: Doping of Cu into Mn-Co spinels improves electrical conductivity as well as thermal expansion match with the Crofer22 APU interconnect.
Titulo: Mn1.4Co1.4Cu0.2O4 spinel protective coating on ferritic stainless steels for solid oxide fuel cell interconnect applications

Sentencas: Good adhesion between the coating and the alloy substrate is achieved by the reactive sintering process using the reduced powders.
Titulo: Mn1.4Co1.4Cu0.2O4 spinel protective coating on ferritic stainless steels for solid oxide fuel cell interconnect applications

Sentencas: Longterm isothermal oxidation experiment and area specific resistance (ASR) measurement are investigated.
Titulo: Mn1.4Co1.4Cu0.2O4 spinel protective coating on ferritic stainless steels for solid oxide fuel cell interconnect applications

Sentencas: The ASR is less than 4 m Omega cm(2) even though the coated alloy undergoes oxidation at 800 degrees C for 530 h and four thermal cycles from 800 degrees C to room temperature.
Titulo: Mn1.4Co1.4Cu0.2O4 spinel protective coating on ferritic stainless steels for solid oxide fuel cell interconnect applications

Sentencas: The Mn1.4Co1.4Cu0.2O4 spinel coatings demonstrate excellent anti-oxidation performance and long-term stability.
Titulo: Mn1.4Co1.4Cu0.2O4 spinel protective coating on ferritic stainless steels for solid oxide fuel cell interconnect applications

Sentencas: It exhibits a promising prospect for the practical application of SOFC alloy interconnect.
Titulo: Mn1.4Co1.4Cu0.2O4 spinel protective coating on ferritic stainless steels for solid oxide fuel cell interconnect applications
